&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Chief Curator and Director of Marketing to plan and execute a social media content strategy that reflects organizational priorities, with content reviewed and approved by the Executive Team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in developing and executing social media strategies, campaigns, and content calendars for multiple brands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create, schedule, and publish multiple posts per week for multiple brands per platform (Instagram, Facebook, LinkedIn, TikTok, YouTube, Pinterest), including graphics, videos, and other multimedia content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify major campaigns and plan strategy for each.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write engaging, on-brand captions and posts for review by the Editorial Director.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure voice consistency across all channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and prepare assets for posts (photos with text, scaling photos, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take video and edit into short reels and other communications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft member newsletter and regular new story letters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor social channels daily, respond to comments and messages in a timely manner, and foster an active, responsive online community.&lt;/li&gt;
