&lt;h1&gt;About the Role&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the Eames Institute, we aim to honor the innovative spirit of Ray and Charles Eames by integrating thoughtful, user-centered design into every digital interaction. As we expand our digital presence, the UX Engineer will serve in a hybrid design and development capacity, playing a key role in shaping intuitive, accessible, and engaging experiences that align with the organization’s mission and values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The UX Engineer will lead digital brand execution and shape core user journeys across our website and other digital platforms. This role requires a unique blend of skills emphasizing the capability to craft complex UX journeys in Figma while being unafraid to make cosmetic changes or build front-end web features. In doing so, you will help ensure a cohesive and impactful user experience across our ecosystem. Reporting to the Digital Engineering Manager and collaborating closely with creative leadership (to be hired) and other cross-functional stakeholders, they will translate institutional goals into compelling, user-friendly digital interactions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By balancing visual storytelling, UX strategy, and technical considerations, this role will ensure that our digital assets meet the highest standards of quality, accessibility, and usability.&lt;/p&gt;
